.e5 idea, and ...b5 is a good later option to resort to if White prevents ...
e5. So, what does White do in the Classical, what's the strategy? Well, White
wants to keep central control and retrain Black's ideas to break out of the
spatial disadvantage. White often plays 'small moves', like h3, Re1, and a4,
to improve his position step by step. White does not have a clear-cut way
forward in the Classical, it's all about flexibility and depends on Black's
