good play. We clear the way for ...Bb7, attacking White's d5-pawn.} c5 11. dxc6
{White does not have time for the manoeuvre Nc3-b1 and c2-c3. We have too much
pressure on the d5-pawn.} Nxc6 {Black is fine in this position, but you need
to avoid a pitfall. If White plays 12.Bg5 , you need to avoid 12...Nxa5?? , as
13.e5! wins for White. 12.Bg5 Qc7 is fine though and leads to equal play.} *

