3.c4 amongst others. After 2...Nf6 , White's overwhelming main move is 3.Nc3
on which we will focus in the Short & Sweet.} 3. Nc3 g6 {After 3...g6 we have
reached the starting position of the Pirc Defense.} 4. Nf3 {White develops the
Knight to its most natural square and gets closer to Kingside castling. White
is not committed to castling Kingsides, obviously, but some more aggressive
setups involving the f-pawn are out of the picture. In comparison, after 4.Be3
White may still play f3 or f4, the pawn structure is not yet determined. After
