the central tension. A closer look reveals that White only has two serious
options: trade with 9.dxe5 or play for the advance 9.d5 . After White has
played the two good but slow moves a4 and h3, keeping the central tension does
not work well. 9.Be3 is possible but not challenging for Black at all. We play
