sides playing for? The central pawn structure is symmetrical and the four
Knights are placed well. The main difference is White's Bishop on e2 versus
our Bishop on g7. White claims that their Bishop is easily activated with Bc4
which helps fight for control over the d5-square. On the other hand, our
Bishop on g7 is staring at the e5-pawn, which looks like a more passive setup.
White's argument is not wrong, but our Bishop is not that badly placed. White
