precise. B. @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/4ppbp/pn1p4/2p3Pp/1p1PP3/1P2BP2/P1PQ3P/
R2NKB1R w KQ - 0 14@@EndFEN@@ 14.c3 bxc3 15.Nxc3 cxd4 16.Bxd4 Bxd4 17.Qxd4 e5
18.Qd2 Be6 also looks fine for Black. C. @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/4ppbp/pn1p4/
2p3Pp/1p1PP3/1P2BP2/P1PQ3P/R2NKB1R w KQ - 0 14@@EndFEN@@ 14.Nf2 a5 15.Be2 Ba6
looks like a logical line too. These are just some ideas to take note of.
There are many options along the way in these fascinating positions. Note that
in these the odd doubled h-pawn plays no role for the moment, as there is far
too much going on in the centre and on the Queenside. White has no time to
target the rather unimportant h5-pawn.} *

